  "texts": [
    "The fraction of correct detections among all detection findings is referred to as accuracy.",
    "It is defined as the ratio of true positive cases (objects belonging to the target category are correctly detected as belonging to the target category) to the sum of true positive cases and false positive cases (objects not belonging to the target category are incorrectly detected as belonging to the target category).",
    "The higher the accuracy value, the more effective the model.",
    "Equation (9) illustrates this.",
    "The recall rate is defined for a certain category as the ratio of projected positive samples to all positive samples."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}